ram\": \"2021 wars\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3391}, {\"ngram\": \"climate crises\", \"from\": 3415, \"to\": 3429}, {\"ngram\": \"especially theCovid-19pandemicwere\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3468}, {\"ngram\": \"refugees\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3486}, {\"ngram\": \"the millions\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3502}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And all those crises-and the resulting escalation in forced migration-were and continue to be made significantly worse by U.S. economic sanctions.\", \"from\": 3505, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all those crises\", \"from\": 3509, \"to\": 3525}, {\"ngram\": \"the resulting escalation\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"forced migration\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3574}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. economic sanctions\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3650}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years before the Rio Olympics, theUN Human Rights Councilexpressed alarm at \\\"the disproportionate and indiscriminate human costs of unilateral sanctions and their negative effects on the civilian population.\\\"\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3673, \"end\": 3685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0783716305115296e-16, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theUN Human Rights Councilexpressed alarm\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"the disproportionate and indiscriminate human costs\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3784}, {\"ngram\": \"unilateral sanctions\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3808}, {\"ngram\": \"their negative effects\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3835}, {\"ngram\": \"the civilian population\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Iran, for example, the U.S. imposed extreme sanctions in 2018 when then-PresidentDonald Trumppulled out of the Iran nuclear deal despite recognition by theUN's nuclear watchdog agencythatTehranwas in compliance with the deal's requirements.\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 4109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3869, \"end\": 3873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9978657916918282, \"rank\": 0.001818227976205694, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 3980, \"end\": 3997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.284204352590528e-16, \"text\": \"Iran nuclear deal\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3886}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3888, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme sanctions\", \"from\": 3905, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"-PresidentDonald\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 3956}, {\"ngram\": \"recognition\", \"from\": 4006, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"theUN's nuclear watchdog\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4045}, {\"ngram\": \"compliance\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4079}, {\"ngram\": \"the deal's requirements\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sanctions' impact on civilians was dire.\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sanctions' impact\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4131}, {\"ngram\": \"civilians\", \"from\": 4135, \"to\": 4144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According toHuman Rights Watch, the sanctions \\\"pose a serious threat to Iranians' right to health and access to essential medicines,\\\" something especially dangerous during the Covid-19 pandemic that was about to hit.\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4227, \"end\": 4235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ira