llionand\", \"from\": 13577, \"to\": 13592}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 13622, \"to\": 13631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And this year, as the 2024 Olympic torch was lit in Paris, the number of forcibly displaced people has soared to 107 million, and Refugee Nation has risen through the ranks to become the15thlargest populationin the world-just behind Egypt.\", \"from\": 13678, \"to\": 13917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13730, \"end\": 13735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999758984, \"rank\": 2.391063944289441e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 13808, \"end\": 13822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Nation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Nation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Nation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Nation\"}, {\"begin\": 13911, \"end\": 13916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.999994925904188, \"rank\": 4.96748957146168e-06, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic torch\", \"from\": 13696, \"to\": 13718}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 13737, \"to\": 13747}, {\"ngram\": \"forcibly displaced people\", \"from\": 13751, \"to\": 13776}, {\"ngram\": \"the ranks\", \"from\": 13841, \"to\": 13850}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 13889, \"to\": 13898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced displacement has been on the rise for a very long time.\", \"from\": 13919, \"to\": 13981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Forced displacement\", \"from\": 13919, \"to\": 13938}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 13951, \"to\": 13959}, {\"ngram\": \"a very long time\", \"from\": 13964, \"to\": 13980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the conditions driving people from their homes-war, repression, economic and climate crises-are on the rise as well.\", \"from\": 13982, \"to\": 14102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the conditions\", \"from\": 13986, \"to\": 14000}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 14009, \"to\": 14015}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes-war\", \"from\": 14021, \"to\": 14036}, {\"ngram\": \"repression\", \"from\": 14038, \"to\": 14048}, {\"ngram\": \"economic and climate crises\", \"from\": 14050, \"to\": 14077}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 14085, \"to\": 14093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2016 war was the biggest reason people were forced to leave their homes.\", \"from\": 14103, \"to\": 14178, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2016 war\", \"from\": 14106, \"to\": 14114}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest reason\", \"from\": 14119, \"to\": 14137}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 14138, \"to\": 14144}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 14166, \"to\": 14177}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2021 wars were still raging, but climate crises and especially theCovid-19pandemicwere creating refugees by the millions.\", \"from\": 14179, \"to\": 14303, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2021 wars\", \"from\": 14182, \"to\": 14191}, {\"ngram\": \"climate crises\", \"from\": 14215, \"to\": 14229}, {\"ngram\": \"especially theCovid-19pandemicwere\", \"from\": 14234, \"to\": 14268}, {\"ngram\": \"refugees\", \"from\": 14278, \"to\": 14286}, {\"ngram\": \"the millions\", \"from\": 14290, \"to\": 14302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And all those crises-and the resulting escalation in forced migration-were and continue to be made significantly worse by U.S. economic sanctions.\", \"from\": 14305, \"to\": 14451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all those crises\", \"from\": 14309, \"to\": 14325}, {\"ngram\": \"the resulting escalation\", \"from\": 14330, \"to\": 14354}, {\"ngram\": \"forced migration\", \"from\": 14358, \"to\": 14374}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. economic sanctions\", \"from\": 14427, \"to\": 14450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years before the Rio Olympics, theUN Human Rights Councilexpressed alarm at \\\"the disproportionate and indiscriminate human costs of unilateral sanctions and their negative effects on the civilian population.\\\"\", \"from\": 14452, \"to\": 14664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14473, \"end\": 14485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0783716305115296e-16, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theUN Human Rights Councilexpressed alarm\", \"from\": 14487, \"to\": 14528}, {\"ngram\": \"the disproportionate and indiscriminate human costs\", \"from\": 14533, \"to\": 14584}, {\"ngram\": \"unilateral sanctions\", \"from\": 14588, \"to\": 14608}, {\"ngram\": \"their negative effects\", \"from\": 14613, \"to\": 14635}, {\"ngram\": \"the civilian population\", \"from\": 14639, \"to\": 14662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Iran, for example, the U.S. imposed extreme sanctions in 2018 when then-PresidentDonald Trumppulled out of the Iran nuclear deal despite recognition by theUN's nuclear watchdog agencythatTehranwas in compliance with the deal's requirements.\", \"from\": 14666, \"to\": 14909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14669, \"end\": 14673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9978657916918282, \"rank\": 0.001818227976205694, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 14780, \"end\": 14797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.284204352590528e-16, \"text\": \"Iran nuclear deal\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 14679, \"to\": 14686}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 14688, \"to\": 14696}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme sanctions\", \"from\": 14705, \"to\": 14722}, {\"ngram\": \"-PresidentDonald\", \"from\": 14740, \"to\": 14756}, {\"ngram\": \"recognition\", \"from\": 14806, \"to\": 14817}, {\"ngram\": \"theUN's nuclear watchdog\", \"from\": 14821, \"to\": 14845}, {\"ngram\": \"compliance\", \"from\": 14869, \"to\": 14879}, {\"ngram\": \"the deal's requirements\", \"from\": 14885, \"to\": 14908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sanctions' impact on civilians was dire.\", \"from\": 14910, \"to\": 14954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sanctions' impact\", \"from\": 14910, \"to\": 14931}, {\"ngram\": \"civilians\", \"from\": 14935, \"to\": 14944}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According toHuman Rights Watch, the sanctions \\\"pose a serious threat to Iranians' right to health and access to essential medicines,\\\" something especially dangerous during the Covid-19 pandemic that was about to hit.\", \"from\": 14955, \"to\": 15171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15027, \"end\": 15035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\", \"score\": 0.8266406855517985, \"rank\": 0.20967986519194423, \"text\": \"Iranians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"toHuman Rights Watch\", \"from\": 14965, \"to\": 14985}, {\"ngram\": \"the sanctions\", \"from\": 14987, \"to\": 15000}, {\"ngram\": \"a serious threat\", \"from\": 15007, \"to\": 15023}, {\"ngram\": \"health\", \"from\": 15046, \"to\": 15052}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 15057, \"to\": 15063}, {\"ngram\": \"essential medicines\", \"from\": 15067, \"to\": 15086}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 15089, \"to\": 15098}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-19 pandemic\", \"from\": 15127, \"to\": 15148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Biden administration lifted some of those Trump-era sanctions, many remain in place and were significantly tightened in April 2024.\", \"from\": 15172, \"to\": 15313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15182, \"end\": 15202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 0.9999729711559084, \"rank\": 2.7029574635060708e-05, \"text\": \"Biden administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those Trump-era sanctions\", \"from\": 15218, \"to\": 15243}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 15260, \"to\": 15265}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 15302, \"to\": 15307}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fourteen members of the Olympic Refugee Team are from Iran.\", \"from\": 15314, \"to\": 15373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15346, \"end\": 15358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 15368, \"end\": 15372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9978657916918282, \"rank\": 0.001818227976205694, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fourteen members\", \"from\": 15314, \"to\": 15330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whatever the specific conditions that forced each of them to leave their homes, U.S. policy is one of the factors that made things worse in their countries.\", \"from\": 15375, \"to\": 15531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the specific conditions\", \"from\": 15384, \"to\": 15407}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 15442, \"to\": 15453}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. policy\", \"from\": 15455, \"to\": 15466}, {\"ngram\": \"the factors\", \"from\": 15477, \"to\": 15488}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 15499, \"to\": 15505}, {\"ngram\": \"their countries\", \"from\": 15515, \"to\": 15530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Afghanistan,sanctions cause famine.\", \"from\": 15533, \"to\": 15571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15536, \"end\": 15547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9948061662362571, \"rank\": 0.005219404162014511, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 15548, \"to\": 15557}, {\"ngram\": \"famine\", \"from\": 15564, \"to\": 15570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, head of the International Rescue Committee and former UK foreign minister David Miliband told the U.S. Senate that the policy of cutting Afghanistan off from financial flows-aka sanctions-was \\\"the proximate cause of thisstarvationcrisis.\\\"\", \"from\": 15572, \"to\": 15819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15593, \"end\": 15623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Rescue Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 15635, \"end\": 15637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9976969147430217, \"rank\": 0.002307973216070998, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 15655, \"end\": 15669, \"title\"